cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.GT, cs.DS

The paper examines the emergence of complex governance regimes in self-governing online communities, which involves aspects of computer science, social science, and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses statistical analysis to identify predictors of community success, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the concentration of power in administrators, which is related to the field of cs.GT (Game Theory).
